title: R.J. Grunts Burgers
text: I paid nearly $16 for a burrito with scrambled eggs and overly fried tater torts. The expectation when you buy a meal in an airport is that it will be inflated in price and underwhelming, so that wasn't the issue. However, there were no employees at the front of house taking orders at the register. There were a couple of kiosks where I first tried to place my order, but the item I wanted to order came with bacon and there was no option to remove this on the kiosk. I waited for about 5 minutes for someone to come out and help me with my order. When the employee finally did come out she asked "did everyone order at the kiosk?" When I said I did not she said "okay order at the kiosk." Then walked away again. Then I waited a little longer for her to come back. I then explained I needed to request no bacon on the burrito I was trying to order and there was no option to do this on the kiosk. She verbally confirmed and walked away. So I went ahead and placed the order at the kiosk and it came out with no bacon, but also no pico de Gallo. So overall, very poor customer service and the staff, and an incorrect, overpriced, order. Would not recommend
